<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1121">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Bowen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-06"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that the Venezuelan chargé was informed there could be no
                            settlement which did not provide for prompt arbitration of pending
                            questions. He was distinctly told that a general arbitration treaty as
                            proposed by Venezuelan Government would be unacceptable at this
                            juncture.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>